  instructions: |-
    To verify and validate an Indian GST Number (GSTIN) from the official Indian Government GST portal and extract the registered business details.
    i. Open the GST verification website URL - https://cleartax.in/gst-number-search/   in a web browser
    ii. Enter the GST Number (GSTIN) - GST Input for Vendor  in the search/verification field
    iii. Obtain the following key details from the webpage:
    – GST Number: The GST Identification Number (GSTIN) provided for verification.
    – Legal Name of Business: The officially registered legal entity name associated with the GSTIN.
    – Trade Name: The business or trade name registered under the GSTIN, if available.
    – GST Status: The current status of the GST registration (e.g., Active, Cancelled, Suspended).
    – Registration Date: The date on which the GST registration became effective.
    – Constitution of Business: The type of business entity (e.g., Proprietorship, Partnership, Private Limited Company).
    – Taxpayer Type: Classification of taxpayer under GST (e.g., Regular, Composition, SEZ, Casual Taxpayer).
    – State/UT: The state or union territory where the GST is registered.
    – Principal Place of Business: The primary registered business address associated with the GSTIN.
    – Jurisdiction: The administrative GST jurisdiction details, if available.
    iv. Output the response to the agent in a JSON object format.
    Additional Instructions:
    – Use only the official Indian Government GST portal for verification.
    – Do not navigate away from the GST verification website URL.
    – If the GST Number is invalid, not found, or inactive, clearly mention the status in the output JSON.
    – If you cannot find all details, return the values for those you can find and return missing details as a blank text string `""`.
    – Use page up and page down instead of scrolling to navigate a page.
    – Do not perform page up/page down more than 1 times. If page navigation does not change the content, immediately stop browsing and return the fields that were found, no exceptions.
    – Do not modify or submit any data other than the GST Number provided for verification.
    – Ensure extracted details exactly match the information displayed on the government portal.
    Expected JSON Output Format:
